			<div id="back-text" class="story-text-container">
				<div id="back-story" class="story-textk">
					<h2>Back Story</h2>
					<p>
						Zak asked Jessica to date at the end of a road trip from 
						So Cal to Nor Cal. At the freeway exit before her apartment, 
						he asked if she had a few minutes to talk. She said yes, and 
						thus began a few interesting minutes as the Denny's he 
						planned to go to didn't work out, and the Starbucks he 
						circled around to find was elusive to his distracted attention. 
					</p>
					<p>
						Jessica suggested they talk back near her house, and he ended 
						up asking her to consider dating him as they walked around. 
						She said yes on the way, and sat down at a bus stop on the 
						corner to ponder this turn of events. 
					</p>
				</div>
			</div>


			<div id="proposal-text" class="story-text-container">
				<div id="proposal-story" class="story-textt">
					<h2>The Proposal</h2>
					<p>
						Is actually quite similar to the backstory. On another drive 
						up to Nor Cal, Zak woke Jessica up at the freeway exit and 
						nonchalantly asked, "Hey, do you have a few minutes to talk?" 
						She went along with it and said yes. 
					</p>
					<p>
						To her surprise, he drove to the familiar landmarks of Denny's,
						Starbucks, and her house.	They walked to the street corner and 
						ended up at the bus stop. Jessica tried to remember which spot 
						she had sat	in, and pointed to the area on her right, saying to 
						Zak, "Hey, I think this is where you were sitting." He looked at 
						her and said, "Was I sitting over there? Or... was I sitting 
						over here," at which point he got down on one knee and asked 
						a question that led to the event of you all invited to witness 
						the covenant they will make before God and before you!
					</p>
				</div>
			</div>
			
			<div id="his-text" class="story-text-container">
